  <description><![CDATA[<p>Very popular with Inghams guests, the Berghof is a traditional hotel representing great value for money in the heart of the village, with a welcoming wood-panelled lounge and cosy bar with open fire.</p>
<h2>Wellness area</h2>
<p>Large renovations have recently been completed, including new wellness, public and guest room areas.</p>
<p>Make the most of your time off the slopes with the hotel's extensive wellness area including indoor and outdoor pools, Finnish saunas, steam baths, aroma sauna and relaxation area.</p>
<h2>Dining</h2>
<p>Enjoy culinary variety throughout the week, delivered with a personal level of service in the homely restaurant.</p>
<p>Emphasis on enjoyment and sustainability means great food made with local produce. Head to the elegant bar and lounge area to try a glass of wine from their extensive national and international wine cellar.</p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>The Hotel Berghof has a great location at one end of <a data-udi="umb://document/f9068cb62c4d4b2299a0ef29fd676ed5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f9068cb62c4d4b2299a0ef29fd676ed5}" title="Mayrhofen">Mayrhofen's</a> main street. You will be just a short walk from the lively resort centre, with a ski bus stop 50 metres away for easy access to the main Penkenbahn.</p>]]></description>
